Dajani-A-M.

Obscure bilateral calcified swellings of paratesticular tissues.

CALCINOSIS: pa.  SCROTUM: pa.

CALCINOSIS: et.  CASTRATION.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: co.  HUMAN.  INFANT.
MALE.  MECONIUM.  PERITONITIS: co.

A case of calcified swellings of the paratesticular tissues
discovered in an infant at different ages is described.  The exact
cause is obscure; and three pathologic conditions are suggested.
Possibly it was due to an old reaction to meconium peritonitis
through a patent processus vaginalis.

